Dorsey McMAHAN, Appellant, v. James A. JOHNSTON, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Alcatraz, California, Appellee. No. 11428. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 2, 1946. Dorsey McMahan, in pro. per., for appellant. Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., and Joseph Karesh, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the District Court is affirmed upon the authority of Swihart v. Johnston, 9 Cir., 150 F.2d 721; Garrison v. Johnston, 9 Cir., 151 F.2d 1011; Wilson v. Johnston, 9 Cir., 154 F.2d 111.
